The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Calcutta cops on toes

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Sept. 8: Calcutta police were put on high alert and a security ring thrown around the city after the blasts in Malegaon.

 Police deployment in front of mosques was doubled in the evening on a day Muslims observed Shab-e-Barat. All mosques across the city are under strict vigil. Officers have been asked to intercept anyone moving around suspiciously, said Pradip Chatterjee, the deputy commissioner of police, headquarters.

 Vigil has been increased at temples, too. 

 Security has also been strengthened at the Writers Buildings, Raj Bhavan and radio and television transmission centres. We have kept all our specialised groups, like the disaster management group, the commandos and the special task force at the ready, said a senior official at the Lalbazar police headquarters.

 The officers of the special branch, the intelligence wing of the city police, and sleuths of the detective departments anti-terrorist cell and the watch section have been asked to keep an eye on certain areas.

 Special measures have been initiated for the Metro Railway. Officers manning the entry and exit points of Metro stations have been put on high alert, the official said. 




